{"type":"message","id":"afc40c52","parentId":"5483dfbe","timestamp":"2026-03-23T21:01:14.850Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the most recent pulse log while the pulse is running.","thinkingSignature":"d8b0d9280179993f2d0fb005db2fd7a9d236eccd7d795ec44095ab6fb5869d16"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oi0bysnshv6a_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-23 165102.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oi0bysnshv6a_2","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"cool-reef","timeout":55000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":443,"output":112,"cacheRead":11887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12442,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774299671540}}
{"type":"message","id":"355a8a44","parentId":"afc40c52","timestamp":"2026-03-23T21:01:14.874Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oi0bysnshv6a_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-23 165102\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: TIC (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most impactful single action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n2. There's a key insight about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n3. The immediate next action is the TIC Experiment\r\n4. Pending actions include writing PowerShell wrapper, defining significance scoring, tuning λ, etc.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action that advances the goals is implementing the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on the pulse logs. This is specifically called out as:\r\n- \"NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\"\r\n- Success criteria are defined (>70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction)\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist:\r\n- `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md` - the new doc with the hypothesis\r\n- `logs/pulse_*.md` - the pulse log files to analyze\r\n\r\nI need to create a TIC classifier that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs (last 20)\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant (stable/recurring) vs variant (changing)\r\n3. Tests prediction of next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nThe most concrete file to create would be a TIC implementation script or a test document. Given the PowerShell context and the need for concrete action, I should create:\r\n1. A TIC classifier implementation, or\r\n2. A test plan for the TIC experiment\r\n\r\nGiven the emphasis on file edits and the PowerShell wrapper mention, I'll create a TIC classifier script. Let me create a PowerShell script that implements the basic TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nActually, looking more carefully - the goal mentions implementing TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files. This is a concrete, specific action. I should create a script that does this analysis.\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC experiment script that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant patterns (things that repeat across pulses)\r\n\r\n\r\n3. Classifies content as invariant vs variant\r\n4. Tests prediction capability\r\n\r\nI'll focus on developing a script that systematically extracts and categorizes pulse log content, creating a foundational framework for the TIC experiment. The script will provide a structured approach to testing the compression-causality hypothesis by analyzing temporal invariance in the pulse logs.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC Experiment is the critical next step for Phase 1 advancement, but there's no implementation yet. The hypothesis is clear: causal structure IS invariant structure, and we need to test this on the pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a PowerShell script that implements the Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) classifier to analyze pulse logs and classify content as invariant vs variant.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$PulseCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogsPath = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# --- Phase 1: Load pulse logs ---\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Loading last $PulseCount pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogsPath -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n    Select-Object -First $PulseCount\r\n\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Host \"ERROR: Need at least 5 pulse logs for analysis\" -ForegroundColor Red\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Found $($pulseFiles.Count) pulse logs\"\r\n\r\n# Parse pulse content into structured data\r\n$pulses = @()\r\nforeach ($file in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw\r\n    $pulses += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        Name = $file.Name\r\n        Content = $content\r\n        Lines = ($content -split \"`n\").Trim() | Where-Object { $_ -ne \"\" }\r\n        Timestamp = $file.LastWriteTime\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Phase 2: Extract features for invariance detection ---\r\nWrite-Host \"`n=== Extracting features ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\n\r\n# Tokenize and count occurrences across pulses\r\n$allTokens = @{}\r\nforeach ($pulse in $pulses) {\r\n    $tokens = $pulse.Lines | ForEach-Object { $_ -split '\\s+' } | \r\n        Where-Object { $_.Length -gt 3 }\r\n    foreach ($token in $tokens) {\r\n        $t = $token.ToLower() -replace '[^a-z0-9]', ''\r\n        if ($t) {\r\n            if ($allTokens.ContainsKey($t)) {\r\n                $allTokens[$t]++\r\n            } else {\r\n                $allTokens[$t] = 1\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Phase 3: Classify invariant vs variant ---\r\nWrite-Host \"`n=== Classification Results ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\n\r\n$invariantThreshold = [math]::Ceiling($PulseCount * 0.5)  # Appears in >50% of pulses\r\n$variantThreshold = [math]::Floor($PulseCount * 0.3)      # Appears in <30% of pulses\r\n\r\n$invariants = @()\r\n$variants = @()\r\n$contextual = @()\r\n\r\nforeach ($token in $allTokens.Keys | Sort-Object $allTokens.Item($_)-Descending) {\r\n    $count = $allTokens[$token]\r\n    if ($count -ge $invariantThreshold) {\r\n        $invariants += [PSCustomObject]@{Token=$token; Count=$count; Ratio=[math]::Round($count/$PulseCount,2)}\r\n    } elseif ($count -le $variantThreshold\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 16:51:28\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774299674870}}
